    "causal_summary": "The only two WITH RECURSIVE consumers in the memory backend are read paths with measurable inefficiencies. getNeighborBoosts (lib/search/causal-boost.ts:431) recurses with ON ce.source_id = cw.node_id OR ce.target_id = cw.node_id, which prevents single-index use on every hop; the live graph measured 10,240 causal edges with max degree 22, so an indexed two-query-per-hop BFS is estimated at 0.5-2ms - at or below the CTE. collectDependents (lib/storage/memo.ts:192) runs an unbounded recursive CTE and wouldCreateCycle fires per insert, yet dependency_edges and memoization_records both held zero rows when measured (2026-06-10). Source evidence: z_future/sqlite-to-turso research.md gap 6 and 004 - gap-alternatives.md section 4.",
